A_360 - As regards the names of the parties, instead of using &ldquo;republican&rdquo;, &ldquo;democrats&rdquo;, it would be better to use imaginary names for the names of the parties and decide which are the key concepts around which the party will have to be based party (e.g. &ldquo;safety at work&rdquo; or &ldquo;protection of human relations&rdquo;, or &ldquo;protection of the environment in relation to new technologies&rdquo;, etc...). In this way, having each political group have a well-defined focus, dialogue and collaboration produce significantly better results. Some examples of party names: &ldquo;octagon party&rdquo;, &ldquo;blue bell party&rdquo;...